= Disciplined Machine Learning
[https://haozhu10015.github.io Hao Zhu] and [https://nr.informatik.uni-freiburg.de/people/joschka-boedecker Joschka Boedecker], [https://uni-freiburg.de/ University of Freiburg]

This webpage contains the material and basic information about the course /Disciplined Machine Learning/; more details and up to date information will be posted on [https://ilias.uni-freiburg.de/ ILIAS].

== Announcements

- The course will be offered in the winter semester of 2026. The exact schedule will be announced later.
- If you want to find something to do before the lecture begins, you can start reading chapter 1 of the [https://haozhu10015.github.io/dmlbook/ textbook], or get familiar with the Python library [https://www.cvxpy.org/ +CVXPY+].

== Textbook
The textbook is [https://haozhu10015.github.io/dmlbook/ /Disciplined Machine Learning/] written by Hao Zhu and Joschka Boedecker, available online.

You will not need to consult any other books or materials for the course, but if you are eager to read more, we highly recommend the book [https://www.stanford.edu/~boyd/cvxbook/ /Convex Optimization/] by Stephen Boyd and Lieven Vandenberghe, which is freely available online, or in hard copy from your favorite bookstore.
